               <p>766. <persName id="def1-766-18390204" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-766-18390204" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-766-18390204" type="age" value="36"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-766-18390204" type="surname" value="HOLLIDAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-766-18390204" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">THOMAS HOLLIDAY</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18390204-766-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390204-766-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390204-766-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18390204-cd-211" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-766-offence-1 t18390204-cd-211"></join>29th of January</rs>, 3 bottles, value 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; and 2 regulators, value 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18390204-name-1309" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1309" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1309" type="surname" value="HARPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1309" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-766-offence-1 t18390204-name-1309"></join>William Harper</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1310" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1310" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1310" type="surname" value="RESTIEAUX"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1310" type="given" value="GEORGE JOHN"></interp>GEORGE JOHN RESTIEAUX</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable E</hi> 49.) On the morning of the 29th of January, about a quarter past seven o'clock, I apprehended the prisoner in Broad-street, St. Giles's—he said he lived in Red Lion-street, Holborn, and then at No. 26, Bedford-street—I wont to Bedford-street,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183902040192"></xptr>
               <p>and found he lived there—I there found three copper water-bottles and two regulators, in a basket in a cupboard, covered with some rubbish, in the two-pair of stairs room—I found his wife there with his children.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did not he tell you exactly in what part of the house he lived? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, I have no recollection of it—I am quite sure he did not say it was the two-pair of stairs—(<hi rend="italic">looking at his deposition</hi>)—this is my hand-writing—it was read over to me—(<hi rend="italic">The depo<lb></lb>sition being ready stated, "He said it was on the two-pair of stairs"</hi>)—I do not recollect his saying so—I am certain I told the Magistrate the truth—I have no doubt the prisoner did tell me so.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1311" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1311" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1311" type="surname" value="HARPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1311" type="given" value="DOROTHY"></interp>DOROTHY HARPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a widow, and keep a house in Bedford-street, Red Lion-square—the prisoner and his wife lodged with me on the second floor—I saw the room the officer searched—it was the room the prisoner occupied.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1312" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1312" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1312" type="surname" value="HARPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1312" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HARPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a stove manufacturer, and live in King Wil<lb></lb>liam-street. The prisoner came into my service nearly four months back—I discharged him on the 26th of January—the articles produced are mine—they are worth 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he had no authority to remove them from the premises.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> You have a great quantity of these things? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I had things similar to these made for a patent stove—Wright and Nash, of Oxford-street, purchase of me, and may have the same things—I have no partner—Mr. Joyce has not been in partnership with me since May—I did not discharge the prisoner for fraud.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1313" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1313" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1313" type="surname" value="HULLS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1313" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HULLS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a coppersmith, and live in Union-street. These articles were made in my factory, for Mr. Harper.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Have you made for any other firm? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No. (The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
